there's going to be a war, Sirius?

242
00:26:58,993 --> 00:27:02,036
It feels like it did before.

243
00:27:06,250 --> 00:27:08,042
You keep it.

244
00:27:08,544 --> 00:27:12,922
Anyway, I suppose
you're the young ones now.

245
00:27:15,134 --> 00:27:16,968
I'll see you at the train.

246
00:27:20,055 --> 00:27:21,556
I love you.

247
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:13,441
I'm surprised the Ministry's
still letting you walk around free.

248
00:28:13,609 --> 00:28:15,109
Better enjoy it while you can.

249
00:28:15,277 --> 00:28:18,571
I expect there's a cell in Azkaban
with your name on it.

250
00:28:21,158 --> 00:28:25,119
- What'd l tell you? Complete nutter.
- Just stay away from me!

251
00:28:26,330 --> 00:28:28,164
It's only Malfoy.

252
00:28:50,813 --> 00:28:51,979
Hi, guys.

253
00:28:52,147 --> 00:28:53,815
- Hey, Neville.
- Hey there, Neville.

254
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:08,413
What is it?

255
00:29:10,582 --> 00:29:13,835
 What's what?
That. Pulling the carriage.

256
00:29:14,670 --> 00:29:17,004
Nothing's pulling the carriage, Harry.

257
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,690
You're not going mad.

258
00:29:38,277 --> 00:29:40,528
I can see them too.

259
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:44,365
You're just as sane as l am.

260
00:29:59,882 --> 00:30:02,216
What an interesting necklace.

261
00:30:02,759 --> 00:30:04,927
It's a charm, actually.

262
00:30:06,305 --> 00:30:07,889
Keeps away the Nargles.

263
00:30:11,685 --> 00:30:13,186
Hungry.

264
00:30:13,854 --> 00:30:15,813
I hope there's pudding.

265
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:18,649
What's a Nargle?

266
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:20,401
HERMlONE
No idea.

267
00:30:33,123 --> 00:30:34,749
Good evening, children.

268
00:30:36,043 --> 00:30:38,753
Now, we have two changes
in staffing this year.

269
00:30:38,921 --> 00:30:41,964
We're pleased to welcome back
Professor Grubbly-Plank...

270
00:30:42,132 --> 00:30:44,717
...who'll be taking
Care of Magical Creatures...

271
00:30:44,885 --> 00:30:48,346
...while Professor Hagrid
is on temporary leave.

272
00:30:49,181 --> 00:30:53,184
We also wish to welcome our new
Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher...

273
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:04,779
Now, as usual, our caretaker, Mr. Filch,
has asked me to remind you-

274
00:31:17,459 --> 00:31:18,793
She was at my hearing.

275
00:31:18,961 --> 00:31:20,169
She works for Fudge.

276
00:31:20,337 --> 00:31:26,050
UMBRlDGE: Thank you, headmaster,
for those kind words of welcome.

277
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:31,097
And how lovely to see all your bright...

278
00:31:31,265 --> 00:31:34,100
...happy faces smiling up at me.

279
00:31:34,476 --> 00:31:39,647
I'm sure we're all going
to be very good friends.

280
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:47,863
The Ministry of Magic
has always considered...

281
00:31:48,031 --> 00:31:53,661
...the education of young witches
and wizards to be of vital importance.

282
00:31:53,996 --> 00:31:56,289
Although each headmaster...

283
00:31:56,456 --> 00:32:01,294
...has brought something new
to this historic school...

284
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:13,556
Let us preserve
what must be preserved...

285
00:32:13,724 --> 00:32:17,226
...perfect what can be perfected...

286
00:32:17,394 --> 00:32:21,606
...and prune practices
that ought to be...

287
00:32:21,773 --> 00:32:23,566
...prohibited.

288
00:32:33,035 --> 00:32:35,202
That really was most illuminating.

289
00:32:35,370 --> 00:32:39,707
 llluminating? What a load of waffle.
- What's it mean?

290
00:32:40,459 --> 00:32:42,627
Magic is forbidden in the corridors...

291
00:32:42,794 --> 00:32:46,380
It means the Ministry's
interfering at Hogwarts.

292
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:07,902
Dean, Seamus.

293
00:33:08,195 --> 00:33:10,321
- Good holiday?
All right.

294
00:33:10,697 --> 00:33:12,907
Better than Seamus', anyway.

295
00:33:16,745 --> 00:33:20,039
- Why not?
- Let me see. Uh, because of you.

296
00:33:20,457 --> 00:33:23,834
The Daily Prophet's been saying a lot
of things about you and Dumbledore.

297
00:33:24,002 --> 00:33:25,336
What, your mum believes them?

298
00:33:25,504 --> 00:33:27,421
Nobody was there the night Cedric died.

299
00:33:27,589 --> 00:33:30,675
I guess you should read the Prophet,
then, like your stupid mother.

300
00:33:54,491 --> 00:33:56,909
- You all right?
- Fine.

301
00:33:57,077 --> 00:33:59,870
Seamus was bang out of order, mate.

302
00:34:00,455 --> 00:34:04,208
- But he'll come through, you'll see.
- l said, l'm fine, Ron.

303
00:34:07,879 --> 00:34:12,299
Right. I'll just leave you
to your thoughts, then.

304
00:34:23,603 --> 00:34:25,604
VOICES WHISPERING]

305
00:34:40,704 --> 00:34:41,746
Harry.

306
00:34:57,179 --> 00:34:59,346
Bring it over here. Over here.

307
00:35:00,265 --> 00:35:02,349
Oh, go on, Seamus. Go on, get it.

308
00:35:18,784 --> 00:35:20,201
Good morning, children.

309
00:35:22,204 --> 00:35:27,374
Ordinary Wizarding Level examinations.

310
00:35:27,542 --> 00:35:30,127
O- W-Ls.

311
00:35:30,295 --> 00:35:34,882
More commonly known as OWLs.

312
00:35:35,050 --> 00:35:38,177
Study hard and you will be rewarded.

313
00:35:38,512 --> 00:35:43,766
Fail to do so,
and the consequences may be severe.

314
00:35:49,356 --> 00:35:54,401
Your previous instruction in this subject
has been disturbingly uneven.

315
00:35:54,569 --> 00:35:56,737
But you'll be pleased to know,
from now on...

316
00:35:56,905 --> 00:36:00,407
...you will be following a carefully
structured, Ministry-approved...

317
00:36:00,575 --> 00:36:03,244
...course of defensive magic. Yes?

318
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:07,206
There's nothing in here
about using defensive spells?

319
00:36:07,374 --> 00:36:08,916
Using spells? Ha-ha!

320
00:36:09,084 --> 00:36:12,545
Well, l can't imagine why you would
need to use spells in my classroom.

321
00:36:14,256 --> 00:36:15,840
We're not gonna use magic?

322
00:36:16,007 --> 00:36:21,011
You'll be learning about defensive spells
in a secure, risk-free way.

323
00:36:21,179 --> 00:36:23,931
What use is that?
If we're attacked, it won't be risk-free.

324
00:36:24,099 --> 00:36:27,059
UMBRlDGE: Students will raise their
hands when they speak in my class.

325
00:36:30,689 --> 00:36:33,107
It is the view of the Ministry...

326
00:36:33,275 --> 00:36:36,026
...that a theoretical knowledge
will be sufficient...

327
00:36:36,194 --> 00:36:38,153
...to get you through your examinations...

328
00:36:38,321 --> 00:36:40,781
...which, after all,
is what school is all about.

329
00:36:40,949 --> 00:36:43,742
And how's theory supposed to prepare us
for what's out there?

330
00:36:43,910 --> 00:36:45,953
There is nothing out there, dear.

331
00:36:46,121 --> 00:36:49,123
Who do you imagine
wants to attack children like yourself?

332
00:36:49,291 --> 00:36:52,585
Oh, l don't know. Maybe Lord Voldemort.

333
00:37:03,263 --> 00:37:07,766
Now, let me make this quite plain.

334
00:37:08,310 --> 00:37:09,768
You have been told...

335
00:37:09,936 --> 00:37:15,316
...that a certain dark wizard
is at large once again.

336
00:37:15,483 --> 00:37:20,613
- This is a lie.
- lt's not a lie. l saw him. l fought him.

337
00:37:20,780 --> 00:37:22,406
UMBRlDGE:
Detention, Mr. Potter.

338
00:37:22,574 --> 00:37:24,742
Cedric Diggory dropped dead
of his own accord?

339
00:37:24,910 --> 00:37:27,328
Cedric Diggory's death
was a tragic accident.

340
00:37:27,495 --> 00:37:29,663
It was murder. Voldemort killed him.

341
00:37:29,831 --> 00:37:31,332
Enough!

342
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,667
Enough.

343
00:37:33,835 --> 00:37:37,463
See me later, Mr. Potter. My office.

344
00:38:02,906 --> 00:38:04,114
UMBRlDGE:
Come in.

345
00:38:09,371 --> 00:38:11,288
Good evening, Mr. Potter.

346
00:38:11,915 --> 00:38:13,207
Sit.

347
00:38:20,882 --> 00:38:24,802
You're going to be doing some lines
for me today, Mr. Potter.

348
00:38:24,970 --> 00:38:26,845
No, not with your quill.

349
00:38:27,055 --> 00:38:30,265
Going to be using
a rather special one of mine.

350
00:38:35,397 --> 00:38:36,814
Now...

351
00:38:37,774 --> 00:38:43,654
...l want you to write,
"I must not tell lies."

352
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:47,616
How many times?

353
00:38:48,076 --> 00:38:52,746
Well, let's say for as long as it takes
for the message to sink in.

354
00:38:54,749 --> 00:38:56,417
You haven't given me any ink.

355
00:38:56,584 --> 00:38:58,085
Oh, you won't need any ink.

356
00:39:49,304 --> 00:39:50,804
Yes?

357
00:39:58,146 --> 00:40:01,523
- Nothing.
- That's right.

358
00:40:02,442 --> 00:40:06,403
Because you know, deep down...

359
00:40:06,571 --> 00:40:08,655
...you deserve to be punished.

360
00:40:09,824 --> 00:40:11,992
Don't you, Mr. Potter?

361
00:40:16,206 --> 00:40:17,831
Go on.

362
00:40:26,841 --> 00:40:29,134
 Skiving Snackboxes.
- Sweets that make you ill.

363
00:40:29,302 --> 00:40:30,928
Get out of class whenever you like.

364
00:40:31,096 --> 00:40:34,848
Obtain hours of pleasure
from unprofitable boredom.

365
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:37,184
Care for another?

366
00:40:37,352 --> 00:40:39,269
 l'm not asking you
to write all of it for me.

367
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:40,479
HERMlONE:
Oh, please.

368
00:40:40,647 --> 00:40:43,023
 l've been busy studying
for these stupid OWL exams.

369
00:40:43,525 --> 00:40:45,317
I'll do the introduction. That's all.

370
00:40:45,485 --> 00:40:49,238
Hermione, you're honestly
the most wonderful person I've ever met.

371
00:40:49,405 --> 00:40:53,659
- And if l'm ever rude to you again...
- l'll know you've gone back to normal.

372
00:40:58,706 --> 00:41:00,791
What's wrong with your hand?

373
00:41:01,334 --> 00:41:02,793
Nothing.

374
00:41:04,045 --> 00:41:05,963
The other hand.

375
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:10,300
- You've got to tell Dumbledore.
- No.

376
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:12,678
Dumbledore's got enough
on his mind right now.

377
00:41:12,846 --> 00:41:14,972
I don't want to give
Umbridge the satisfaction.

378
00:41:15,140 --> 00:41:17,558
Bloody hell, Harry.
The woman's torturing you.

379
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:21,687
- lf the parents knew about this...
- l haven't got any of those, have l, Ron?

380
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:26,942
Harry, you've got to report this.

381
00:41:27,110 --> 00:41:30,654
- lt's perfectly simple. You're being-
- No, it's not.

382
00:41:30,822 --> 00:41:33,657
Hermione, whatever this is,
it's not simple.

383
00:41:34,701 --> 00:41:36,743
You don't understand.

384
00:41:39,330 --> 00:41:41,248
Then help us to.

385
00:41:55,972 --> 00:41:57,848
Dear Padfoot...

386
00:41:58,391 --> 00:42:00,100
...l hope you're all right.

387
00:42:00,268 --> 00:42:04,897
It's starting to get colder here.
Winter is definitely on the way.

388
00:42:07,525 --> 00:42:12,279
In spite of being back at Hogwarts,
l feel more alone than ever.

389
00:42:13,781 --> 00:42:16,450
I know you, of all people,
will understand.

390
00:42:50,526 --> 00:42:52,736
Hello, Harry Potter.

391
00:42:55,365 --> 00:42:59,993
- Your feet. Aren't they cold?
- Bit.

392
00:43:00,912 --> 00:43:04,957
Unfortunately, all my shoes
have mysteriously disappeared.

393
00:43:05,500 --> 00:43:08,585
I suspect Nargles are behind it.

394
00:43:14,926 --> 00:43:17,678
 What are they?
They're called Thestrals.

395
00:43:19,264 --> 00:43:24,309
They're quite gentle, really, but people
avoid them because they're a bit...

396
00:43:27,230 --> 00:43:28,855
Different.

397
00:43:31,985 --> 00:43:34,361
But why can't the others see them?

398
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:38,031
They can only be seen
by people who've seen death.

399
00:43:40,159 --> 00:43:42,786
So you've known someone
who's died, then?

400
00:43:42,954 --> 00:43:44,579
My mum.

401
00:43:45,123 --> 00:43:50,043
She was quite an extraordinary witch,
but she did like to experiment...

402
00:43:50,211 --> 00:43:53,505
...and one day,
one of her spells went badly wrong.

403
00:43:53,673 --> 00:43:56,049
- l was 9.
- l'm sorry.

404
00:43:56,634 --> 00:43:58,844
Yes, it was rather horrible.

405
00:43:59,012 --> 00:44:04,349
I do feel very sad about it sometimes,
but I've got Dad.

406
00:44:06,561 --> 00:44:08,562
We both believe you, by the way.

407
00:44:12,275 --> 00:44:15,277
That He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named
is back, and you fought him...

408
00:44:15,445 --> 00:44:18,572
...and the Ministry and the Prophet
are conspiring against you.

409
00:44:18,740 --> 00:44:23,076
Thanks. It seems you're about
the only ones that do.

410
00:44:23,244 --> 00:44:24,578
I don't think that's true.

411
00:44:26,956 --> 00:44:30,083
But l suppose
that's how he wants you to feel.

412
00:44:30,251 --> 00:44:32,044
What do you mean?

413
00:44:32,670 --> 00:44:34,546
Well, if I were You-Know-Who...

414
00:44:35,006 --> 00:44:38,592
...l'd want you to feel cut off
from everyone else...

415
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:41,470
...because if it's just you alone...

416
00:44:42,305 --> 00:44:44,639
...you're not as much of a threat.

417
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:07,037
- Do you ever stop eating?
- What? l'm hungry.

418
00:45:10,416 --> 00:45:11,458
Harry.

419
00:45:13,294 --> 00:45:14,544
Can l join you?

420
00:45:16,464 --> 00:45:19,591
UMBRlDGE: Pardon me, professor,
but what exactly are you insinuating?

421
00:45:19,759 --> 00:45:22,552
McGONAGALL: I am merely requesting
that when it comes to my students...

422
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:26,973
...you conform to the prescribed
disciplinary practices.

423
00:45:27,141 --> 00:45:28,809
UMBRlDGE:
So silly of me, but it sounds...

424
00:45:28,976 --> 00:45:33,105
...as if you're questioning my authority
in my own classroom...

425
00:45:33,272 --> 00:45:34,606
...Minerva.

426
00:45:34,774 --> 00:45:39,236
Not at all, Dolores,
merely your medieval methods.

427
00:45:39,487 --> 00:45:41,988
I am sorry, dear.

428
00:45:42,156 --> 00:45:45,492
But to question my practices
is to question the Ministry...

429
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:48,787
...and by extension, the minister himself.

430
00:45:48,955 --> 00:45:50,539
I am a tolerant woman...

431
00:45:50,706 --> 00:45:55,794
...but the one thing
I will not stand for is disloyalty.

432
00:45:57,547 --> 00:45:59,339
Disloyalty.

433
00:46:01,050 --> 00:46:05,011
Things at Hogwarts
are far worse than I feared.

434
00:46:05,179 --> 00:46:08,682
Cornelius will want
to take immediate action.

435
00:46:20,069 --> 00:46:21,987
What's happened to Dumbledore?

436
00:46:22,155 --> 00:46:24,698
Having already revolutionized...

437
00:46:24,866 --> 00:46:27,784
...the teaching
of Defense Against the Dark Arts...

438
00:46:28,202 --> 00:46:33,582
...Dolores Umbridge will,
as high inquisitor, have powers...

439
00:46:34,375 --> 00:46:39,379
...to address the seriously falling
standards at Hogwarts School.

440
00:46:47,138 --> 00:46:49,306
Just one question, dear.

441
00:46:49,474 --> 00:46:53,685
You've been in this post
how long, exactly?

442
00:47:00,485 --> 00:47:05,572
You applied first for the Defense Against
the Dark Arts post, is that correct?

443
00:47:05,740 --> 00:47:07,741
Yes.

444
00:47:08,159 --> 00:47:10,785
But you were unsuccessful?

445
00:47:11,996 --> 00:47:13,413
Obviously.

446
00:47:46,781 --> 00:47:50,200
Could you please predict something
for me?

447
00:47:51,953 --> 00:47:53,119
I'm sorry?

448
00:47:58,376 --> 00:48:00,585
Move those mouths.

449
00:48:06,717 --> 00:48:09,803
One teensy little prophecy?

450
00:48:15,685 --> 00:48:17,143
Pity.

451
00:48:17,687 --> 00:48:20,105
No, wait. Wait, no.
I think I do see something.

452
00:48:20,273 --> 00:48:22,482
Yes, l do. Something dark.

453
00:48:22,733 --> 00:48:27,279
You are in grave danger.

454
00:48:28,739 --> 00:48:30,490
Lovely.

455
00:48:40,668 --> 00:48:42,836
Cho. What's going on?

456
00:48:43,004 --> 00:48:45,338
It's Professor Trelawney.

457
00:49:07,820 --> 00:49:09,237
Ooh!

458
00:49:15,161 --> 00:49:18,663
Sixteen years l've lived and taught here.

459
00:49:18,831 --> 00:49:21,750
Hogwarts is my home.

460
00:49:23,669 --> 00:49:25,545
You can't do this.

461
00:49:27,006 --> 00:49:29,257
Actually, I can.

462
00:49:38,142 --> 00:49:39,517
Something you'd like to say?

463
00:49:39,685 --> 00:49:42,354
Oh, there are several things
I would like to say.

464
00:49:42,897 --> 00:49:44,272
There... Shh. Shh.

465
00:49:58,412 --> 00:50:03,083
Professor McGonagall, might l ask you
to escort Sybil back inside?

466
00:50:04,377 --> 00:50:06,836
Sybil, dear. This way.

467
00:50:07,004 --> 00:50:08,505
Thank you.

468
00:50:09,674 --> 00:50:13,718
UMBRlDGE: Dumbledore, may l remind
you that under the terms...

469
00:50:13,886 --> 00:50:17,138
...of Educational Decree Number 23,
as enacted by the minister-

470
00:50:17,306 --> 00:50:20,475
You have the right
to dismiss my teachers.

471
00:50:20,643 --> 00:50:24,229
You do not, however, have the authority
to banish them from the grounds.

472
00:50:24,397 --> 00:50:27,440
That power remains with the headmaster.

473
00:50:29,443 --> 00:50:30,694
For now.

474
00:50:37,118 --> 00:50:39,119
Don't you all have studying to do?

475
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:40,453
Professor.

476
00:50:42,289 --> 00:50:43,415
Professor?

477
00:50:43,874 --> 00:50:46,668
Professor Dumbledore. Professor!

478
00:50:46,836 --> 00:50:48,962
Professor Dumbledore.

479
00:50:59,640 --> 00:51:01,766
HERMlONE:
That foul, evil, old gargoyle.

480
00:51:02,309 --> 00:51:04,519
We're not learning how
to defend ourselves.

481
00:51:04,687 --> 00:51:07,313
We're not learning how
to pass our OWLs.

482
00:51:07,690 --> 00:51:09,733
She's taking over the entire school.

483
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:14,571
FUDGE Security has been
and will remain the Ministry's top priority.

484
00:51:14,739 --> 00:51:17,574
Furthermore,
we have convincing evidence...

485
00:51:17,742 --> 00:51:20,618
...that these disappearances
are the work...

486
00:51:20,786 --> 00:51:24,164
...of notorious
mass murderer Sirius Black.

487
00:51:24,915 --> 00:51:26,499
SlRlUS:
Harry.

488
00:51:26,709 --> 00:51:28,418
Sirius.

489
00:51:29,170 --> 00:51:31,838
- What are you doing here?
SlRlUS: Answering your letter.

490
00:51:32,006 --> 00:51:34,924
You said you were worried
about Umbridge. What's she doing?

491
00:51:35,092 --> 00:51:37,010
Training you to kill half-breeds?

492
00:51:37,178 --> 00:51:40,180
- She's not letting us use magic at all.
SlRlUS: Well, l'm not surprised.

493
00:51:40,514 --> 00:51:44,559
The latest intelligence is that Fudge
doesn't want you trained in combat.

494
00:51:44,727 --> 00:51:45,769
Combat?

495
00:51:46,270 --> 00:51:49,189
What does he think,
we're forming some sort of wizard army?

496
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:50,732
That's exactly what he thinks.

497
00:51:50,900 --> 00:51:54,861
That Dumbledore is assembling
his own forces to take on the Ministry.

498
00:51:55,362 --> 00:51:58,698
He's becoming more paranoid
by the minute.

499
00:51:59,033 --> 00:52:02,535
The others wouldn't want me
telling you this, Harry...

500
00:52:03,037 --> 00:52:05,872
...but things aren't going at all well
with the Order.

501
00:52:06,040 --> 00:52:08,708
Fudge is blocking the truth
at every turn...

502
00:52:08,876 --> 00:52:12,879
...and these disappearances
are just how it started before.

503
00:52:13,672 --> 00:52:17,008
Voldemort is on the move.

504
00:52:17,301 --> 00:52:18,343
Well, what can we do?

505
00:52:19,720 --> 00:52:20,929
Someone's coming.

506
00:52:21,096 --> 00:52:23,223
I'm sorry I can't be of more help.

507
00:52:23,390 --> 00:52:28,394
But for now, at least,
it looks like you're on your own.

508
00:52:39,907 --> 00:52:42,242
He really is out there, isn't he?

509
00:52:44,078 --> 00:52:46,746
We've got to be able
to defend ourselves.

510
00:52:47,331 --> 00:52:51,084
And if Umbridge refuses to teach us how,
we need someone who will.

511
00:53:08,102 --> 00:53:10,270
Harry.

512
00:53:19,864 --> 00:53:22,240
 This is mad.
Who'd wanna be taught by me?

513
00:53:22,408 --> 00:53:23,616
I'm a nutter, remember?

514
00:53:23,784 --> 00:53:28,288
Look on the bright side: you can't
be any worse than old toad face.

515
00:53:28,539 --> 00:53:32,000
- Thanks, Ron.
- l'm here for you, mate.

516
00:53:32,501 --> 00:53:34,836
Who's supposed to be meeting us, then?

517
00:53:35,004 --> 00:53:37,130
HERMlONE:
Just a couple of people.

518
00:53:42,136 --> 00:53:43,469
Lovely spot.

519
00:53:47,308 --> 00:53:49,434
Thought it would be safer
off the beaten track.

520
00:53:49,602 --> 00:53:51,769
Matey, come back here.

521
00:53:57,818 --> 00:53:59,319
Um...

522
00:54:00,195 --> 00:54:01,362
Hi.

523
00:54:01,780 --> 00:54:04,657
So you all know why we're here.

524
00:54:04,825 --> 00:54:06,075
We need a teacher.

525
00:54:07,786 --> 00:54:09,954
A proper teacher.

526
00:54:10,247 --> 00:54:13,416
One who's had experience defending
themselves against the Dark Arts.

527
00:54:13,584 --> 00:54:15,335
- Why?
Why?

528
00:54:15,502 --> 00:54:17,587
Because You-Know-Who's back,
you tosspot.

529
00:54:17,755 --> 00:54:19,380
- So he says.
HERMlONE: So Dumbledore says.

530
00:54:19,548 --> 00:54:21,633
So Dumbledore says because he says.

531
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:24,177
The point is, where's the proof?

532
00:54:25,554 --> 00:54:28,598
If Potter could tell us more
about how Diggory got killed...

533
00:54:31,685 --> 00:54:35,355
I'm not gonna talk about Cedric, so if
that's why you're here, clear out now.

534
00:54:35,522 --> 00:54:36,689
Come on, Hermione.

535
00:54:36,857 --> 00:54:39,067
They're here because they think
I'm some sort of freak.

536
00:54:39,234 --> 00:54:41,861
Is it true you can produce
a Patronus Charm?

537
00:54:45,199 --> 00:54:46,616
HERMlONE:
Yes.

538
00:54:48,077 --> 00:54:49,535
I've seen it.

539
00:54:49,703 --> 00:54:51,829
Blimey, Harry.
I didn't know you could do that.

540
00:54:52,498 --> 00:54:56,626
And he killed a basilisk, with the sword
in Dumbledore's office.

541
00:54:56,794 --> 00:54:58,044
It's true.

542
00:54:58,212 --> 00:55:00,964
Third year, he fought off
about a hundred Dementors at once.

543
00:55:02,257 --> 00:55:05,051
Last year, he really did fight off
You-Know-Who in the flesh.

544
00:55:05,219 --> 00:55:06,552
Wait.

545
00:55:07,221 --> 00:55:11,766
Look, it all sounds great
when you say it like that...

546
00:55:11,934 --> 00:55:15,520
...but the truth is,
most of that was just luck.

547
00:55:15,771 --> 00:55:19,524
I didn't know what I was doing
half the time. I nearly always had help.

548
00:55:19,692 --> 00:55:23,194
- He's just being modest.
- No, Hermione, l'm not.

549
00:55:25,739 --> 00:55:30,410
Facing this stuff in real life
is not like school.

550
00:55:31,453 --> 00:55:34,914
In school, if you make a mistake,
you can just try again tomorrow.

551
00:55:35,082 --> 00:55:36,582
But out there...

552
00:55:37,167 --> 00:55:40,461
...when you're a second away
from being murdered...

553
00:55:40,629 --> 00:55:44,340
...or watching a friend die
right before your eyes...

554
00:55:47,094 --> 00:55:48,928
You don't know what that's like.

555
00:55:58,689 --> 00:56:00,606
HERMlONE:
You're right, Harry, we don't.

556
00:56:01,358 --> 00:56:03,443
That's why we need your help.

557
00:56:03,610 --> 00:56:06,529
Because if we're going to have
any chance at beating...

558
00:56:08,741 --> 00:56:09,907
...Voldemort...

559
00:56:13,328 --> 00:56:15,079
He's really back?

560
00:56:36,643 --> 00:56:38,853
Right. First we need to find
a place to practice...

561
00:56:39,021 --> 00:56:40,646
...where Umbridge won't find out.

562
00:56:40,814 --> 00:56:42,982
- The Shrieking Shack.
- lt's too small.

563
00:56:43,150 --> 00:56:46,110
- Forbidden Forest?
- Not bloody likely.

564
00:56:46,278 --> 00:56:48,362
Harry, what happens
if Umbridge does find out?

565
00:56:48,530 --> 00:56:49,697
HERMlONE:
Who cares?

566
00:56:50,324 --> 00:56:55,161
I mean, it's sort of exciting, isn't it,
breaking the rules?

567
00:56:55,329 --> 00:56:57,622
Who are you and what have you done
with Hermione?

568
00:56:58,332 --> 00:57:02,001
Anyway, at least we know
one positive thing that came from today.

569
00:57:02,169 --> 00:57:03,461
What's that?

570
00:57:05,172 --> 00:57:07,840
Cho couldn't take her eyes off you,
could she?

571
00:57:10,594 --> 00:57:13,679
 Right. Over the next few days,
we should each come up...

572
00:57:13,847 --> 00:57:16,682
...with a couple of possibilities
of places we can practice.

573
00:57:16,850 --> 00:57:20,686
We've got to make sure, wherever it is,
there's no chance she can find us.

574
00:57:20,854 --> 00:57:22,688
Will do, Harry.

575
00:57:31,406 --> 00:57:35,535
 All student organizations
are henceforth disbanded.

576
00:57:35,702 --> 00:57:38,329
Any student in noncompliance
will be expelled.

577
00:57:39,706 --> 00:57:41,499
Watch where you're going, Longbottom.

578
00:58:17,703 --> 00:58:21,956
HERMlONE: You've done it, Neville.
You found the Room of Requirement.

579
00:58:22,124 --> 00:58:23,249
The what?

580
00:58:23,417 --> 00:58:25,835
HERMlONE: lt's also known as
the Come and Go Room.

581
00:58:26,003 --> 00:58:29,422
The Room of Requirement only appears
when a person has real need of it.

582
00:58:29,590 --> 00:58:32,258
And it's always equipped
for the seeker's needs.

583
00:58:32,426 --> 00:58:36,179
So say you really needed the toilet...

584
00:58:37,347 --> 00:58:42,185
Charming, Ronald.
But, yes, that is the general idea.

585
00:58:42,352 --> 00:58:47,231
It's brilliant. lt's like Hogwarts
wants us to fight back.

586
00:58:58,285 --> 00:58:59,785
Expelliarmus.

587
00:59:00,287 --> 00:59:01,621
Whoa!

588
00:59:04,917 --> 00:59:06,292
I'm hopeless.

589
00:59:06,460 --> 00:59:10,254
You're just flourishing your wand
too much. Try it like this. Expelliarmus.

590
00:59:13,634 --> 00:59:17,637
UMBRlDGE: You will please copy
the approved text four times...

591
00:59:17,804 --> 00:59:20,806
...to ensure maximum retention.

592
00:59:21,183 --> 00:59:24,894
- There will be no need to talk.
- No need to think's more like it.

593
00:59:25,062 --> 00:59:27,897
NEVILLE Expelliarmus.
UMBRlDGE: Wands away.

594
00:59:40,035 --> 00:59:43,120
Stunning is one of the most useful spells
in your arsenal.

595
00:59:43,288 --> 00:59:45,498
It's a wizard's bread and butter, really.

596
00:59:45,666 --> 00:59:49,252
So, um, come on, then, Nigel.
Give it your best shot.

597
00:59:55,759 --> 00:59:57,176
Stupefy!

598
01:00:02,057 --> 01:00:06,519
Good. Not bad at all, Nigel. Well done.

599
01:00:11,858 --> 01:00:13,985
Don't worry. l'll go easy on you.

600
01:00:14,361 --> 01:00:16,362
Thanks, Ronald.

601
01:00:19,032 --> 01:00:21,200
 Come on, Ron.
Come on, Ron.

602
01:00:21,368 --> 01:00:24,245
 You can do it.
Come on, Ron.

603
01:00:24,788 --> 01:00:26,831
- One Sickle.
- You're on.

604
01:00:33,880 --> 01:00:34,922
Stupefy.

605
01:00:40,887 --> 01:00:42,888
- Thank you.
- Shut up.

606
01:00:43,265 --> 01:00:47,893
I let her do that.
It's good manners, isn't it?

607
01:00:50,105 --> 01:00:52,648
It was completely intentional.

608
01:01:18,258 --> 01:01:21,218
UMBRlDGE: Up you come.
Would you like a cup of tea?

609
01:01:23,513 --> 01:01:27,475
Now, focus on a fixed point
and try again.

610
01:01:28,060 --> 01:01:29,226
Expelliarmus.

611
01:01:31,605 --> 01:01:34,148
Very good. Keep your concentration.

612
01:01:36,276 --> 01:01:37,777
Great.

613
01:01:39,029 --> 01:01:40,613
A little higher.

614
01:01:46,578 --> 01:01:48,079
Whoa!

615
01:01:49,122 --> 01:01:51,957
I'm okay. I'm okay.

616
01:02:09,976 --> 01:02:12,603
 Stupefy.
Stupefy.

617
01:02:14,147 --> 01:02:17,525
UMBRlDGE: Those wishing tojoin
the Inquisitorial Squad for extra credit...

618
01:02:17,692 --> 01:02:20,569
...may sign up
in the high inquisitor's office.

619
01:02:20,737 --> 01:02:22,363
Diminuendo.

620
01:02:28,286 --> 01:02:32,581
Working hard is important, but there's
something that matters even more:

621
01:02:32,749 --> 01:02:34,959
Believing in yourself.

622
01:02:35,127 --> 01:02:37,253
 Expelliarmus.
Levicorpus. Got it.

623
01:02:37,421 --> 01:02:39,004
Think of it this way.

624
01:02:39,172 --> 01:02:43,175
Every great wizard in history
has started out...

625
01:02:43,510 --> 01:02:47,388
...as nothing more
than what we are now: students.

626
01:02:47,556 --> 01:02:50,516
If they can do it, why not us?

627
01:03:00,652 --> 01:03:02,445
 Stupefy.
- Expelliarmus.

628
01:03:04,614 --> 01:03:05,990
Expelliarmus.

629
01:03:08,702 --> 01:03:10,202
Expelliarmus.

630
01:03:15,709 --> 01:03:17,042
Reducto.

631
01:03:30,557 --> 01:03:33,559
 Expelliarmus.
- Expelliarmus.

632
01:03:33,727 --> 01:03:36,061
Expelliarmus.

633
01:03:39,983 --> 01:03:41,525
Expelliarmus.

634
01:03:45,906 --> 01:03:49,283
Fantastic, Neville. Well done, man.

635
01:03:50,911 --> 01:03:53,078
So that's it for this lesson.

636
01:03:53,246 --> 01:03:55,748
Now, we're not gonna be meeting again
until after the holidays.

637
01:03:57,125 --> 01:04:00,085
So just keep practicing on your own
as best you can.

638
01:04:00,253 --> 01:04:03,589
And well done, everyone.
Great, great work.

639
01:04:08,428 --> 01:04:09,845
Well done, mate.

640
01:04:10,013 --> 01:04:11,430
Thanks.

641
01:04:17,103 --> 01:04:19,480
See you after Christmas.

642
01:04:28,949 --> 01:04:30,991
See you in the Common Room, Harry.

643
01:04:32,410 --> 01:04:35,120
- Thanks a lot, Harry.
- No worries.

644
01:04:35,789 --> 01:04:36,789
Merry Christmas.

645
01:04:36,957 --> 01:04:39,250
 Thank you so much.
Not at all. Merry Christmas.

646
01:04:39,709 --> 01:04:42,086
 Thank you, Harry.
- Thank you. Merry Christmas.

647
01:04:42,254 --> 01:04:44,129
- Merry Christmas.
Have a good Christmas.

648
01:04:44,297 --> 01:04:46,882
 Have a great Christmas, Luna.
We've been thinking.

649
01:04:47,050 --> 01:04:49,468
We could always slip Umbridge
some Puking Pastilles.

650
01:04:49,636 --> 01:04:52,304
Or Fever Fudge. They give you
massive, pus-filled boils-

651
01:04:52,472 --> 01:04:54,974
Sounds great, guys.
Would you excuse me?

652
01:05:05,944 --> 01:05:10,656
Are you all right? I heard Umbridge
gave you a rough time the other day.

653
01:05:10,824 --> 01:05:13,200
Yeah. l'm okay.

654
01:05:13,910 --> 01:05:16,704
Anyway, it's worth it.

655
01:05:22,043 --> 01:05:25,212
It's just, learning all this...

656
01:05:26,006 --> 01:05:29,466
...makes me wonder whether,
if he'd known it...

657
01:05:29,634 --> 01:05:32,344
Cedric did know this stuff.

658
01:05:32,929 --> 01:05:35,347
He was really good.

659
01:05:35,974 --> 01:05:38,684
It's just, Voldemort was better.

660
01:05:43,231 --> 01:05:45,024
You're a really good teacher, Harry.

661
01:05:46,318 --> 01:05:49,194
I've never been able
to stun anything before.

662
01:05:58,371 --> 01:06:00,039
Mistletoe.

663
01:06:03,543 --> 01:06:05,461
Probably full of Nargles, though.

664
01:06:06,546 --> 01:06:08,213
What are Nargles?

665
01:06:08,923 --> 01:06:10,674
No idea.

666
01:06:32,697 --> 01:06:34,907
Well, how was it?

667
01:06:35,659 --> 01:06:37,409
Wet.

668
01:06:37,827 --> 01:06:39,578
I mean, she was sort of crying.

669
01:06:39,954 --> 01:06:41,914
That bad at it, are you?

670
01:06:42,082 --> 01:06:44,833
I'm sure Harry's kissing
was more than satisfactory.

671
01:06:47,671 --> 01:06:49,838
Cho spends half her time
crying these days.

672
01:06:50,006 --> 01:06:52,257
You'd think a bit of snogging
would cheer her up.

673
01:06:53,760 --> 01:06:56,595
Don't you understand
how she must be feeling?

674
01:07:01,017 --> 01:07:04,478
Well, obviously
she's feeling sad about Cedric...

675
01:07:04,646 --> 01:07:07,731
...and confused about liking Harry
and guilty about kissing him...

676
01:07:07,899 --> 01:07:11,110
...conflicted because Umbridge might
sack her mum from the Ministry...

677
01:07:11,277 --> 01:07:15,030
...and frightened of failing her OWLs
because she's worrying about everything.

678
01:07:16,950 --> 01:07:20,536
One person couldn't feel all that.
They'd explode.

679
01:07:20,704 --> 01:07:23,956
Just because you've got
the emotional range of a teaspoon...

680
01:07:40,432 --> 01:07:41,432
Harry.

681
01:07:50,191 --> 01:07:53,277
SlRlUS:
Voldemort may be after something.

682
01:07:53,945 --> 01:07:56,947
Something he didn't have last time.

683
01:07:57,782 --> 01:07:59,032
Harry.

684
01:08:00,660 --> 01:08:01,952
Harry.

685
01:08:33,026 --> 01:08:36,445
 In the dream,
were you standing next to the victim...

686
01:08:36,613 --> 01:08:38,113
...or looking down at the scene?

687
01:08:38,573 --> 01:08:41,533
Neither. lt was like l...

688
01:08:42,118 --> 01:08:44,203
Will you please just tell me
what's happening?

689
01:08:44,370 --> 01:08:46,705
Everard, Arthur's on guard duty tonight.

690
01:08:46,873 --> 01:08:49,291
Make sure he's found
by the right people.

691
01:08:49,459 --> 01:08:51,043
 Sir.
Phineas.

692
01:08:51,211 --> 01:08:53,504
You must go to your portrait
at Grimmauld Place.

693
01:08:53,671 --> 01:08:56,298
Tell them that Arthur Weasley
is gravely injured...

694
01:08:56,466 --> 01:09:00,636
...and his children will be arriving there
soon by Portkey.

695
01:09:00,804 --> 01:09:03,889
 They've got him, Albus.
It was close, but they think he'll make it.

696
01:09:04,057 --> 01:09:06,225
What's more,
the Dark Lord failed to acquire it.

697
01:09:06,392 --> 01:09:07,601
Oh, thank goodness. Next we need to-

698
01:09:07,769 --> 01:09:08,811
VOLDEMORT WHISPERS]

699
01:09:08,978 --> 01:09:10,229
Look at me!

700
01:09:16,528 --> 01:09:18,737
What's happening to me?

701
01:09:26,621 --> 01:09:28,497
You wished to see me, headmaster?

702
01:09:28,665 --> 01:09:33,585
Oh, Severus. l'm afraid we can't wait.
Not even till the morning.

703
01:09:33,962 --> 01:09:36,880
Otherwise, we'll all be vulnerable.

704
01:09:41,636 --> 01:09:43,262
It appears there's a connection...

705
01:09:43,429 --> 01:09:45,764
...between the Dark Lord's mind
and your own.

706
01:09:45,932 --> 01:09:50,102
Whether he is, as yet, aware of this
connection is, for the moment, unclear.

707
01:09:50,436 --> 01:09:53,480
Pray he remains ignorant.

708
01:09:53,648 --> 01:09:56,942
You mean, if he knows about it, then...

709
01:09:57,402 --> 01:10:01,780
- ...he'll be able to read my mind?
- Read it, control it...

710
01:10:01,948 --> 01:10:03,824
...unhinge it.

711
01:10:03,992 --> 01:10:07,369
In the past, it was often
the Dark Lord's pleasure...

712
01:10:07,537 --> 01:10:09,788
...to invade the minds of his victims...

713
01:10:09,956 --> 01:10:13,542
...creating visions designed
to torture them into madness.

714
01:10:14,669 --> 01:10:19,464
Only after extracting the last exquisite
ounce of agony...

715
01:10:19,632 --> 01:10:23,927
...only when he had them literally
begging for death, would he finally...

716
01:10:24,095 --> 01:10:25,304
...kill them.

717
01:10:26,306 --> 01:10:28,724
Used properly,
the power of Occlumency...

718
01:10:28,892 --> 01:10:32,394
...will help shield you
from access or influence.

719
01:10:32,562 --> 01:10:37,316
In these lessons, I will attempt
to penetrate your mind.

720
01:10:37,901 --> 01:10:40,986
You will attempt to resist.

721
01:10:41,279 --> 01:10:42,738
Prepare yourself.

722
01:10:45,491 --> 01:10:46,700
Legilimens.

723
01:10:54,834 --> 01:10:58,420
Concentrate, Potter. Focus.

724
01:11:24,322 --> 01:11:25,948
Ho, ho, ho. Merry Christmas.

725
01:11:27,158 --> 01:11:29,826
Here we go.

726
01:11:29,994 --> 01:11:32,162
Daddy's back. Oh.

727
01:11:35,333 --> 01:11:38,961
Sit down, everybody, sit down.
That's it. Now, presents.

728
01:11:39,128 --> 01:11:43,507
 And a nice big box for Ron.
Big box for you. And, um...

729
01:11:46,302 --> 01:11:48,512
Fred and George. Come on, open up.

730
01:11:48,680 --> 01:11:50,973
- l want to see your faces.
Yes.

731
01:11:51,140 --> 01:11:53,558
 Try it on.
Thanks, Mum. It's perfect.

732
01:11:53,726 --> 01:11:58,021
- Just what he wanted, actually.
- Yeah. Right. Thanks, Mum.

733
01:11:58,189 --> 01:12:01,066
 Come on, then, everybody.
Let's clear this away.

734
01:12:01,234 --> 01:12:03,235
Oh, Harry, Harry.

735
01:12:03,403 --> 01:12:05,320
There you are.

736
01:12:06,322 --> 01:12:08,156
- Happy Christmas.
- Thank you.

737
01:12:08,741 --> 01:12:10,575
- Lovely to have you with us.
- Thank you.

738
01:12:10,743 --> 01:12:12,744
Now, Daddy. Pass that to Daddy.

739
01:12:12,912 --> 01:12:14,621
 Thank you.
Has everybody got?

740
01:12:14,789 --> 01:12:16,164
Fred? George?

741
01:12:16,332 --> 01:12:18,875
- Hermione.
A Christmas toast.

742
01:12:19,043 --> 01:12:20,919
To Mr. Harry Potter...

743
01:12:21,921 --> 01:12:24,756
...without whom I would not be here.

744
01:12:28,344 --> 01:12:30,679
- Harry.
Harry.

745
01:12:30,847 --> 01:12:32,097
Harry.

746
01:12:33,099 --> 01:12:35,684
 That is delicious.
I shall be needing some more of that.

747
01:12:35,852 --> 01:12:38,228
Daddy, don't forget last Christmas.

748
01:12:39,147 --> 01:12:41,898
I can't understand
why you don't want to wear it, Ronald.

749
01:12:43,359 --> 01:12:45,193
I look like a bloody idiot, that's why.

750
01:12:45,361 --> 01:12:47,195
HERMlONE:
No more than usual, Ron.

751
01:12:47,405 --> 01:12:49,239
I don't know why...

752
01:12:55,246 --> 01:12:59,833
Nasty brat, standing there
as bold as brass.

753
01:13:00,001 --> 01:13:04,755
Harry Potter,
the boy who stopped the Dark Lord.

754
01:13:04,922 --> 01:13:07,924
Friend of Mudbloods
and blood-traitors alike.

755
01:13:08,342 --> 01:13:10,969
- lf my poor mistress only knew...
SlRlUS: Kreacher!

756
01:13:11,137 --> 01:13:13,972
That's enough of your bile.
Away with you!

757
01:13:14,140 --> 01:13:16,141
Of course, master.

758
01:13:16,309 --> 01:13:20,979
Kreacher lives to serve
the noble house of Black.

759
01:13:23,316 --> 01:13:25,192
Sorry about that.

760
01:13:25,777 --> 01:13:29,446
He never was very pleasant,
even when I was a boy.

761
01:13:29,781 --> 01:13:31,865
Not to me, anyway.

762
01:13:32,700 --> 01:13:34,659
What, you grew up here?

763
01:13:34,827 --> 01:13:37,079
SlRlUS:
This is my parents' house.

764
01:13:37,413 --> 01:13:41,249
I offered it to Dumbledore
as headquarters for the Order.

765
01:13:42,376 --> 01:13:45,670
About the only useful thing
I've been able to do.

766
01:13:47,048 --> 01:13:49,424
This is the Black family tree.

767
01:13:50,343 --> 01:13:52,469
My deranged cousin.

768
01:13:52,637 --> 01:13:55,347
I hated the lot of them.

769
01:13:55,515 --> 01:14:00,227
My parents with their pure-blood mania.

770
01:14:03,439 --> 01:14:07,234
My mother did that after I ran away.

771
01:14:09,570 --> 01:14:11,446
Charming woman.

772
01:14:12,698 --> 01:14:14,366
I was 16.

773
01:14:15,201 --> 01:14:16,618
Where did you go?

774
01:14:18,704 --> 01:14:19,955
Round your dad's.

775
01:14:21,457 --> 01:14:24,000
I was always welcome at the Potters'.

776
01:14:24,877 --> 01:14:27,629
I see him so much in you, Harry.

777
01:14:28,256 --> 01:14:30,465
You are so very much alike.

778
01:14:31,384 --> 01:14:33,385
I'm not so sure.

779
01:14:34,428 --> 01:14:35,887
Sirius, when l was...

780
01:14:38,724 --> 01:14:43,228
When I saw Mr. Weasley attacked,
I wasn't just watching.

781
01:14:44,397 --> 01:14:45,897
I was the snake.

782
01:14:46,732 --> 01:14:49,693
And afterwards, in Dumbledore's office...

783
01:14:49,861 --> 01:14:54,072
...there was a moment
when l wanted to-

784
01:14:59,203 --> 01:15:02,080
This connection
between me and Voldemort.

785
01:15:02,748 --> 01:15:06,334
What if the reason for it
is that I am becoming more like him?

786
01:15:07,670 --> 01:15:12,591
I just feel so angry all the time.

787
01:15:12,758 --> 01:15:17,304
And what if, after everything
that I've been through...

788
01:15:17,471 --> 01:15:21,057
...something's gone wrong inside me?
What if I'm becoming bad?

789
01:15:23,686 --> 01:15:26,938
I want you to listen to me
very carefully, Harry.

790
01:15:28,107 --> 01:15:31,109
You're not a bad person.

791
01:15:31,944 --> 01:15:36,281
You're a very good person
who bad things have happened to.

792
01:15:36,908 --> 01:15:38,033
You understand?

793
01:15:40,119 --> 01:15:45,165
Besides, the world isn't split
into good people and Death Eaters.

794
01:15:45,333 --> 01:15:49,794
We've all got both light and dark
inside of us.

795
01:15:50,546 --> 01:15:53,798
What matters
is the part we choose to act on.

796
01:15:55,760 --> 01:15:58,053
That's who we really are.

797
01:16:01,807 --> 01:16:03,558
Harry, time to go.

798
01:16:05,311 --> 01:16:09,606
When all this is over,
we'll be a proper family.

799
01:16:09,774 --> 01:16:11,358
You'll see.

800
01:16:12,485 --> 01:16:13,860
Come on.

801
01:16:26,916 --> 01:16:28,750
VOICES WHISPERING]

802
01:16:51,315 --> 01:16:52,482
Really?

803
01:16:52,650 --> 01:16:55,277
HERMlONE:
Harry. Harry.

804
01:16:55,444 --> 01:16:57,362
Hagrid's back.

805
01:17:00,324 --> 01:17:02,158
I'm sorry.

806
01:17:16,382 --> 01:17:19,551
UMBRlDGE:
I will say this one last time.

807
01:17:19,844 --> 01:17:22,220
I'm ordering you to tell me
where you've been.

808
01:17:22,388 --> 01:17:25,390
I told you. I've been away for me health.

809
01:17:25,725 --> 01:17:29,894
- Your health?
- Yeah. Bit of fresh air, you know.

810
01:17:30,062 --> 01:17:34,899
Oh, yes. As gamekeeper,
fresh air must be difficult to come by.

811
01:17:36,944 --> 01:17:39,446
If l were you,
I shouldn't get too used to being back.

812
01:17:39,613 --> 01:17:42,907
In fact, l mightn't bother
unpacking at all.

813
01:18:01,844 --> 01:18:04,929
This is top-secret, right?

814
01:18:05,848 --> 01:18:08,224
Dumbledore sent me
to parley with the giants.

815
01:18:08,392 --> 01:18:09,893
- Giants?
Shh.

816
01:18:11,062 --> 01:18:12,103
You found them?

817
01:18:12,271 --> 01:18:16,191
Well, they're not that hard to find, to be
perfectly honest. They're so big, see?

818
01:18:17,068 --> 01:18:20,111
I tried to convince them
to join the cause.

819
01:18:20,279 --> 01:18:22,947
But l wasn't the only one
that was trying to win them over.

820
01:18:23,657 --> 01:18:25,575
- Death Eaters?
Yes.

821
01:18:26,035 --> 01:18:29,371
Trying to persuade them
to join You-Know-Who.

822
01:18:29,872 --> 01:18:32,248
- Did they?
- l gave them Dumbledore's message.

823
01:18:32,416 --> 01:18:36,503
Suppose some of them remember
he was friendly to them. l suppose.

824
01:18:40,132 --> 01:18:41,424
And they did this to you?

825
01:18:42,051 --> 01:18:43,093
Not exactly, no.

826
01:18:44,470 --> 01:18:48,306
Oh, go on, you have it, then,
you dozy dog.

827
01:19:02,279 --> 01:19:04,406
It's changing out there.

828
01:19:04,824 --> 01:19:06,408
Just like last time.

829
01:19:07,868 --> 01:19:09,494
There's a storm coming, Harry.

830
01:19:10,246 --> 01:19:13,331
We'd all best be ready when she does.

831
01:19:50,327 --> 01:19:53,371
 We have confirmed
that 10 high-security prisoners...

832
01:19:53,539 --> 01:19:56,374
...in the early hours of yesterday evening
did escape.

833
01:19:56,542 --> 01:20:00,211
And of course, the Muggle prime minister
has been alerted to the danger.

834
01:20:00,379 --> 01:20:02,464
We strongly suspect...

835
01:20:03,299 --> 01:20:05,300
...that the breakout was engineered...

836
01:20:05,468 --> 01:20:09,679
...by a man with personal experience
in escaping from Azkaban...

837
01:20:09,847 --> 01:20:14,058
...notorious mass murderer Sirius Black...

838
01:20:15,519 --> 01:20:19,063
...cousin of escapee Bellatrix Lestrange.

839
01:20:30,201 --> 01:20:32,494
Dumbledore warned Fudge
this could happen.

840
01:20:32,661 --> 01:20:35,830
He's gonna get us all killed
just because he can't face the truth.

841
01:20:35,998 --> 01:20:37,123
Harry.

842
01:20:38,375 --> 01:20:39,626
I, uh...

843
01:20:40,836 --> 01:20:42,837
I wanted to apologize.

844
01:20:43,422 --> 01:20:47,592
Now even me mum says the Prophet's
version of things don't add up.

845
01:20:47,760 --> 01:20:53,681
So, what I'm really trying to say
is that I believe you.

846
01:21:00,606 --> 01:21:02,232
Neville?

847
01:21:14,787 --> 01:21:16,955
Fourteen years ago...

848
01:21:17,122 --> 01:21:21,376
...a Death Eater
named Bellatrix Lestrange...

849
01:21:21,544 --> 01:21:24,754
...used a Cruciatus Curse on my parents.

850
01:21:25,297 --> 01:21:29,300
She tortured them for information...

851
01:21:29,468 --> 01:21:31,636
...but they never gave in.

852
01:21:33,305 --> 01:21:35,807
I'm quite proud to be their son.

853
01:21:36,767 --> 01:21:40,645
But l'm not sure
I'm ready for everyone to know just yet.

854
01:21:46,569 --> 01:21:50,697
We're gonna make them proud, Neville.
That's a promise.

855
01:21:54,952 --> 01:21:58,663
Make it a powerful memory,
the happiest you can remember.

856
01:21:58,831 --> 01:22:02,250
Allow it to fill you up.
Keep trying, Seamus.

857
01:22:02,418 --> 01:22:03,835
George, your turn now.

858
01:22:05,170 --> 01:22:07,505
Expecto Patronum.

859
01:22:08,424 --> 01:22:11,843
A full-bodied Patronus
is the most difficult to produce...

860
01:22:12,011 --> 01:22:15,847
...but shield forms can also be equally
useful against a variety of opponents.

861
01:22:16,015 --> 01:22:17,265
Wow, that was really good.

862
01:22:17,975 --> 01:22:19,517
Fantastic, Ginny.

863
01:22:19,685 --> 01:22:23,730
Remember, your Patronus can only protect
you for as long as you stay focused.

864
01:22:23,897 --> 01:22:26,190
So focus, Luna.

865
01:22:29,903 --> 01:22:31,613
Think of the happiest thing you can.

866
01:22:31,780 --> 01:22:33,740
Expecto Patronum.

867
01:22:33,907 --> 01:22:36,784
- l'm trying.
l know. lt's good.

868
01:22:36,952 --> 01:22:39,954
This is really advanced stuff, guys.
You're doing so well.

869
01:22:41,957 --> 01:22:44,375
Expecto Patronum.

870
01:23:26,210 --> 01:23:28,753
UMBRlDGE:
I'll make short work of this.

871
01:23:30,089 --> 01:23:32,090
Bombarda Maxima.

872
01:23:50,359 --> 01:23:51,734
Get them.

873
01:23:52,152 --> 01:23:53,653
UMBRlDGE:
Been watching them for weeks.

874
01:23:53,821 --> 01:23:55,738
And see, "Dumbledore's Army"...

875
01:23:56,156 --> 01:23:59,867
...proof of what l've been telling you
right from the beginning, Cornelius.

876
01:24:01,245 --> 01:24:03,287
All your fear-mongering
about You-Know-Who...

877
01:24:03,455 --> 01:24:04,997
...never fooled us for a minute.

878
01:24:05,165 --> 01:24:07,250
We saw your lies for what they were:

879
01:24:07,418 --> 01:24:11,212
A smokescreen for your bid
to seize control of the Ministry.

880
01:24:11,380 --> 01:24:12,422
Naturally.

881
01:24:12,589 --> 01:24:15,133
No, professor.
He had nothing to do with it. It was me.

882
01:24:15,300 --> 01:24:18,970
Most noble of you, Harry, to shield me,
but as has been pointed out...

883
01:24:19,138 --> 01:24:23,975
...the parchment clearly says
"Dumbledore's Army," not "Potter's."

884
01:24:24,143 --> 01:24:26,769
I instructed Harry
to form this organization.

885
01:24:26,937 --> 01:24:30,398
And l, and l alone,
am responsible for its activities.

886
01:24:30,566 --> 01:24:32,400
Dispatch an owl to the Daily Prophet.

887
01:24:32,568 --> 01:24:35,111
If we hurry,
we should still make the morning edition.

888
01:24:35,279 --> 01:24:40,074
Dawlish, Shacklebolt,
you will escort Dumbledore...

889
01:24:40,242 --> 01:24:41,659
...to Azkaban...

890
01:24:42,911 --> 01:24:47,498
...to await trial
for conspiracy and sedition.

891
01:24:47,666 --> 01:24:51,169
Ah. l thought we might hit
this little snag.

892
01:24:52,337 --> 01:24:55,798
You seem to be laboring
under the delusion that I'm going to-

893
01:24:56,341 --> 01:24:57,800
What was the phrase?

894
01:24:57,968 --> 01:24:59,552
- come quietly.

895
01:24:59,720 --> 01:25:01,429
Well, l can tell you this:

896
01:25:01,847 --> 01:25:04,182
I have no intention of going to Azkaban.

897
01:25:04,349 --> 01:25:05,600
Enough of this.

898
01:25:06,101 --> 01:25:07,185
Take him.

899
01:25:18,030 --> 01:25:19,697
Whoa.

900
01:25:20,032 --> 01:25:24,410
Well, you may not like him, minister...

901
01:25:24,578 --> 01:25:26,704
...but you can't deny...

902
01:25:27,247 --> 01:25:29,999
...Dumbledore has got style.

903
01:25:53,857 --> 01:25:58,736
UMBRlDGE: Boys and girls cannot be
within eight inches of each other.

904
01:25:58,904 --> 01:26:02,323
Those wishing to join
the Inquisitorial Squad for extra credit...

905
01:26:02,491 --> 01:26:07,537
Students will be submitted to questioning
about suspected illicit activities.

906
01:26:07,704 --> 01:26:11,999
Any student in noncompliance
will be expelled.

907
01:27:23,196 --> 01:27:24,822
Harry.

908
01:27:31,747 --> 01:27:35,166
 You did everything you could.
No one could win against that old hag.

909
01:27:35,334 --> 01:27:37,668
HERMlONE: Even Dumbledore
didn't see this coming.

910
01:27:38,587 --> 01:27:40,755
Harry, if it's anyone's fault, it's ours.

911
01:27:40,923 --> 01:27:43,007
Yeah, we talked you into it.

912
01:27:43,175 --> 01:27:45,176
Yeah, but l agreed.

913
01:27:45,719 --> 01:27:49,847
I tried so hard to help,
and all it's done is make things worse.

914
01:27:51,892 --> 01:27:54,352
Anyway, that doesn't matter anymore.

915
01:27:55,395 --> 01:27:59,607
Because I don't want to play anymore.
All it does is make you care too much.

916
01:27:59,775 --> 01:28:02,443
And the more you care,
the more you have to lose.

917
01:28:02,611 --> 01:28:05,780
- So maybe it's just better to...
- To what?

918
01:28:08,033 --> 01:28:09,951
To go it alone.

919
01:28:10,702 --> 01:28:12,286
Psst.

920
01:28:16,291 --> 01:28:17,959
Hagrid.

921
01:28:21,713 --> 01:28:24,131
Any idea where he's taking us?

922
01:28:24,299 --> 01:28:27,385
Hagrid, why can't you just tell us?

923
01:28:35,686 --> 01:28:38,354
I've never seen the centaurs so riled.

924
01:28:38,522 --> 01:28:41,065
And they're dangerous
at the best of times.

925
01:28:42,025 --> 01:28:44,360
The Ministry restricts
their territory much more...

926
01:28:44,528 --> 01:28:46,737
...they'll have a full uprising
on their hands.

927
01:28:46,905 --> 01:28:48,572
Hagrid, what's going on?

928
01:28:48,740 --> 01:28:50,950
I'm sorry to be so mysterious, you three.

929
01:28:51,118 --> 01:28:56,080
I wouldn't be bothering you at all with it,
but with Dumbledore gone...

930
01:28:56,748 --> 01:28:59,917
...l'll likely be getting the sack
any day now.

931
01:29:00,085 --> 01:29:03,587
And l just couldn't leave
without telling someone about him.

932
01:29:07,759 --> 01:29:09,427
Grawpy.

933
01:29:11,805 --> 01:29:13,931
Down here, you great buffoon.

934
01:29:19,312 --> 01:29:21,939
Oh, Grawpy.

935
01:29:22,733 --> 01:29:24,442
Brought you some company.

936
01:29:36,788 --> 01:29:39,040
I couldn't just leave him, because-

937
01:29:39,207 --> 01:29:40,958
Because he's my brother.

938
01:29:41,126 --> 01:29:42,251
Blimey.

939
01:29:42,419 --> 01:29:44,462
Well, half brother, really.

940
01:29:44,629 --> 01:29:49,884
He's completely harmless, just like l said.
Little high-spirited, is all.

941
01:29:52,262 --> 01:29:54,513
 Grawpy, that is not polite.
- Hagrid, do something.

942
01:29:54,681 --> 01:29:56,932
We talked about this.
You do not grab, do you?

943
01:29:57,100 --> 01:29:59,351
That's your new friend, Hermione.

944
01:29:59,519 --> 01:30:00,811
Grawpy.

945
01:30:05,150 --> 01:30:06,317
HERMlONE:
Grawp.

946
01:30:08,361 --> 01:30:11,447
Put me down.

947
01:30:15,118 --> 01:30:16,660
Now.

948
01:30:28,840 --> 01:30:29,924
You all right?

949
01:30:31,218 --> 01:30:32,885
Fine.

950
01:30:33,303 --> 01:30:35,596
Just needs a firm hand, is all.

951
01:30:35,764 --> 01:30:38,182
I think you've got an admirer.

952
01:30:40,685 --> 01:30:42,853
You just stay away from her, all right?

953
01:31:12,968 --> 01:31:15,719
He gets his own food and all.

954
01:31:16,972 --> 01:31:20,057
It's company he'll be needing
when l'm gone.

955
01:31:21,393 --> 01:31:23,602
You will look after him, won't you?

956
01:31:24,104 --> 01:31:26,814
I'm the only family he's got.

957
01:31:40,412 --> 01:31:42,246
Feeling sentimental?

958
01:31:45,542 --> 01:31:49,378
- That's private.
- Not to me.

959
01:31:49,671 --> 01:31:53,174
And not to the Dark Lord,
if you don't improve.

960
01:31:55,594 --> 01:31:58,762
Every memory he has access to
is a weapon he can use against you.

961
01:31:58,930 --> 01:32:03,100
You won't last two seconds
if he invades your mind.

962
01:32:04,269 --> 01:32:06,520
You're just like your father.

963
01:32:06,688 --> 01:32:08,480
Lazy, arrogant.

964
01:32:08,648 --> 01:32:10,900
- Don't say a word against my father.
- Weak.

965
01:32:11,067 --> 01:32:13,235
- l'm not weak.
- Then prove it.

966
01:32:13,862 --> 01:32:15,779
Control your emotions.

967
01:32:15,947 --> 01:32:18,908
Discipline your mind.

968
01:32:21,745 --> 01:32:22,953
Legilimens.

969
01:32:30,128 --> 01:32:31,253
Harry.

970
01:32:31,421 --> 01:32:33,130
Sirius.

971
01:32:33,798 --> 01:32:35,132
I may vomit.

972
01:32:35,425 --> 01:32:36,467
Stop it.

973
01:32:37,636 --> 01:32:39,929
Is this what you call control?

974
01:32:40,430 --> 01:32:43,474
We've been at it for hours.
If l could just rest.

975
01:32:43,642 --> 01:32:47,061
The Dark Lord isn't resting.

976
01:32:48,688 --> 01:32:52,024
You and Black, you're two of a kind.
Sentimental children forever whining...

977
01:32:52,192 --> 01:32:54,735
...about how bitterly unfair
your lives have been.

978
01:32:54,903 --> 01:32:58,280
Well, it may have escaped your notice,
